'''Ōmiya Shrine''' (おおみやじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945}} located in Kamishiraiwa, {{ill|lt=Izu City|Q696840|WD=Q696840}}, {{ill|lt=Shizuoka Prefecture|Q131320|WD=Q131320}}.

It is the central shrine of the Shiraiwa district, which roughly corresponds to the former {{ill|lt=Shimoōmi Village|Q11360758|WD=Q11360758}}<ref name="tennen">[http://www.city.izu.shizuoka.jp/gyousei/gyousei_detail000109.html City-Designated Natural Monument] - Izu City</ref>.

=== Overview ===
Many old {{ill|lt=munafuda|Q8008834|WD=Q8008834}} (ridge plaques) are preserved, the oldest of which is inscribed with the 3rd year of {{ill|lt=Kōan|Q389180|WD=Q389180}} (1280) in the {{ill|lt=Kamakura period|Q236205|WD=Q236205}}<ref name="tennen"/><ref name="yuisho">Shrine grounds history inscription</ref>.

Because the nearby {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Kamishiraiwa Site|UNKNOWN}} dates back to the {{ill|lt=Jōmon period|Q52824|WD=Q52824}}, and because there is also a place name “Motomura” in the area, it is considered the oldest shrine established earliest in the surrounding region<ref name="tennen"/><ref name="yuisho"/>.

Before the Edo period, it was called '''Shiraiwa Ōasa Shrine''' (しらいわ おおあさじんじゃ), and together with {{ill|lt=Yōhara Shrine#Related Shrines|Q11541065|WD=Q11541065|lt=Ōasa Shrine}} in Shimo Kanuki, {{ill|lt=Numazu City|Q241037|WD=Q241037}}, it is listed as a candidate for “Ōasa Shrine” in the {{ill|lt=List of Shikinaisha Shrines of Izu Province|Q11380552|WD=Q11380552|lt=Shikinaisha}}<ref name="yuisho"/>. (In the nearby southeastern district (Yahata district), there is also {{ill|lt=Kinomiya Shrine (Yahata, Izu City)|Q119929624|WD=Q119929624|lt=Kinomiya Shrine}}, which is a candidate for another Shikinaisha, “Sugihokowake-no-Mikoto Shrine.”)

The {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=shrine forest|UNKNOWN}} surrounding the shrine buildings is designated as a city natural monument<ref name="tennen"/>.

=== Enshrined Deity ===
* {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto|UNKNOWN}} ({{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Ōkuninushi-no-Kami|UNKNOWN}})

=== Subsidiary Shrines within the Grounds ===
* Kinomiya Shrine  
* Hachiman Shrine  
* Yama Shrine  
* Kumano Shrine  
* Uba Shrine  
* Suwa Shrine  
* Suijin Shrine  
* Kotohira Shrine  
* Inari Shrine  

=== Cultural Properties ===
* The {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=shrine forest|UNKNOWN}} of Ōmiya Shrine (City-designated Natural Monument<ref name="tennen"/>)

=== Festivals ===
* Grand Annual Festival (around October 18)

=== Access ===
* {{ill|lt=Tokai Bus|Q11527778|WD=Q11527778}} (city-commissioned independent operation<ref>[https://www.at-s.com/news/article/shizuoka/932289.html Route Bus Nakaizu Line to Be Independently Operated by Izu City] - Shizuoka Shimbun 2021/7/21</ref>): 2 minutes on foot northeast from the “Kamishiraiwa” bus stop.

